    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Q2 - Drivers'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='1300' maxwidth='1200' minheight='1300' minwidth='1200' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='61462' id='9' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98000' x='1000' y='923'>
            <zone h='61462' id='7' type-v2='layout-basic' w='98000' x='1000' y='923'>
              <zone forceUpdate='true' h='8810' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98000' x='1000' y='923'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='16'>Debt Level, Ad Creative, and Google Campaign Selection Drive Lead Quality</run>
                  <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='16'>Æ </run>
                  <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Q2: What can we learn about the drivers of &quot;lead quality&quot; from this dataset? </run>
                  <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>What segments have differing lead quality rates?</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                  <format attr='background-color' value='#ffffff' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone h='52652' id='5' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98000' x='1000' y='9733'>
                <zone fixed-size='645' h='52652' id='11' is-fixed='true' name='Debt Level' w='54417' x='1000' y='9733'>
                  <layout-cache type-h='fixed' type-w='cell' />
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='background-color' value='#ffffff' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
                <zone h='52652' id='6' name='Widget Creative' w='43583' x='55417' y='9733'>
                  <layout-cache minwidth='240' type-h='fixed' type-w='scalable' />
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='background-color' value='#ffffff' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone forceUpdate='true' h='36692' id='12' type-v2='text' w='98000' x='1000' y='62385'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>FINDINGS </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>1. Lead quality varies significantly based on user characteristics, ad creative, and campaign selection. </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>2. Debt level is the strongest and only statistically significant driver (p = 0.006). </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>3. Users with $70K–$90K debt convert at 13.7%, while users under $10K convert at ~5%. </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>4. The optimal segment is users with $10K–$100K debt. </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>5. Ad creative has a large impact, with a ~9 percentage point difference across creatives. </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>6. BlueMeter performs best (14.1%) and attracts higher-quality users. </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>7. Campaign performance varies widely, with a 3.6x gap between best and worst. </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>8. “Debt Holding Tank” converts at 14.5%, while “DebtReductionInc” converts at 4.0%. </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>9. Factors such as branding, form design, and channel have minimal impact. </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>10. Overall, lead quality is driven by user segment, creative, and campaign choice.</run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              <format attr='background-color' value='#ffffff' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='12' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
